---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Paper"
  description="No paper published yet — first experiment in progress."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-24">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500 mb-4">
        Technical Paper
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100">
        No paper published yet
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 mt-4 max-w-2xl">
        Papers are published after live data collection completes and peer review passes.
        The first experiment is in progress.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex gap-4">
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="text-sm text-amber-500 hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors"
        >
          Our methodology &rarr;
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/misty-step/laboratory"
          class="text-sm text-stone-500 hover:text-stone-700 dark:hover:text-stone-300 transition-colors"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          GitHub repository &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 rounded-lg p-6 text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400">
      <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300 mb-2">Why no paper?</p>
      <p>
        A previous experiment mixed simulated and live data without disclosure. Rather than
        publish compromised findings, we archived those artifacts and restarted with stricter
        data integrity standards. All future papers will cite only live API call data,
        peer-reviewed before publication.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
